<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<project xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0" xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/maven-v4_0_0.xsd">
	<modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>
	<artifactId>ccad-firebird-dss-server-plugin</artifactId>
	<packaging>p2-repository</packaging>
	<name>DSS Server Plugin</name>
	<description>The Data Stream Server (DSS) is responsible for generating the data streams carrying the control data required by the customer premises 
		equipment (CPE) in a digital broadcast system. These data streams include data for which the DSS acts either as a carousel or as a router. The 
		system supports the use of multiple DSSs, where each DSS sits in between the system components that generate the control messages and the edge 
		devices (such as Motorola SEMs, OMs or CMTSs) that ultimately transmit the data streams to CPE. The DSS supports MPEG-2, DSG Broadcast Tunnel 
		and IP Direct transmissions. The DSS provides support for transport streams, in compliance with the MPEG-2 transport stream requirements of 
		ISO 13818-1.
	</description>
